text: Harvey Daniel James Elliott (Born April 4th, 2003, 21 years) is a English professional footballer who plays for Liverpool F.C. as an attacking- midfielder or right-winger. He is known for his technical dribbling skills, incisive passes, and flair with the ball. His career started at Fulham F.C. where he made his senior debut at 16 years and 30 days, against Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. Harvey made 3 appearances for Fulham before he made the move to Liverpool and then going on Loan to Blackburn Rovers F.C. Category:English footballers Category:2003 births Category:Living people
title: Harvey Elliott
